EAU-DE-VIE

The pure, colorless brandies

These utterly delicious, colorless brandies, exceptional when served in a chilled glass add interest to the dinner party. The fra- grance of the fruit is impressive and is captured by the distilling process—we know of nothing that surpasses these Eau- de-Vie at the end of a special dinner. Be- low you will discover the fragrance of the cherry, the pear, the yellow plum, the prune and the haunting wild raspberry flavor of a superb Framboise. They may be expensive—but a bottle goes a long way —an ounce of any of these is worth linger- ing over for an hour at the end of the din- ner party.

COGNACS & BRANDIES Brandy is a distillate of any fruit. Cognac is a distillate of one of the fruits—the grape ~and this product can only be called ‘Cognac’ if it is distilled in a choice and limited area in southwest France, Un- questionably, Cognac is the best brandy of them all, richly endowed with finesse, elegance, delicate aroma and a harmony of taste. If you are seeing the best Cognac of all France, we do not think you can do better than acquiring some of the ‘Single Cask Unblended’—every drop of which was distilled during the excellent 1934 vintage. Do not overlook the remarkable Armagnacs and distillates from other regions.
